<p>I have a text file like mentioned below, and along with that I will pass an input for which I want a corresponding output.</p>  <p>Input file: <code>test.txt</code></p>  <pre><code>abc:abc_1 abcd:abcd_1 1_abcd:1_abcd_bkp xyz:xyz_2 </code></pre>  <p>so if I use <code>abc</code> with the above test.txt file, I want <code>abc_1</code>; and if I pass <code>abcd</code>, I need <code>abcd_1</code> as output.</p>  <p>I tried <code>cat text.txt | grep abc | cut -d":" -f2,2</code>, but I am getting the output </p>  <pre><code>abc_1 abcd_1 1_abcd_bkp </code></pre>  <p>when I want only <code>abc_1</code>.</p>